title: Which will sell more album units in its first week of release: Kanye’s Donda or Drake’s Certified Lover Boy?
description:

Albums are ranked by Album Units, a number that combines digital and physical album sales, digital song sales, and audio streams, using a custom weighting system. If the name of either album is changed, this market will consider the next album released by that artist.

For both albums, the resolution source will be checked at 12:00 PM ET on the Friday following the album’s appearance on Rolling Stone’s weekly Friday-Thursday album units rankings (e.g. if Donda comes out on Fri, August 13, 2021, its first weekly sales will be checked at 12:00 PM ET, Fri, August 20, 2021).

title: What will the fully diluted market cap of Opensea’s token be 1 week after it starts trading?
description:

The lower bound for this market is $1,000,000,000 and the upper bound is $7,000,000,000. The date by which the token is actively traded refers to the first date the token reaches over $10,000 in volume according to CoinGecko. The fully diluted market cap 1 week after this date, at 12:00 PM ET, will be used for this market’s resolution. For example, if the Opensea token began actively trading on a Tuesday (in ET), the fully diluted market cap of the token would be checked at 12:00 PM ET the following Tuesday in order to resolve this market. If the total supply is infinite, the circulating supply/non-diluted market cap will be used instead to resolve this market. If the CoinGecko website is unavailable at the time of this check, or relevant data is unavailable on CoinGecko, CoinMarketCap will be used instead. If both CoinGecko and CoinMarketCap are down, or relevant data is unavailable, then another credible source will be chosen.

If Opensea does not release a token by December 31, 2021, 11:59:59 PM ET, the market will resolve to $4,000,000,000.

You can use the calculator to the right (underneath the Buy modal) to calculate how each Long or Short Token price corresponds with Opensea token’s fully diluted market cap value in USD. Long and Short shares will settle proportionally to the outcome value if the final value is between these bounds, but if the final value exceeds either the upper or lower bound, the price of each Outcome Token is capped at $1 and $0. title: Will the US have fewer than 1000 COVID-19 cases on any day on or before September 1?
description:

title: Will more than 2.5 million people travel through a TSA checkpoint on any day before August?
description:
This is a market on whether more than 2.5 million people will travel through a TSA checkpoint on any single day between July 8, 2022 and July 31, 2022 (inclusive).

The resolution source for this market will be the daily checkpoint throughput as measured by the US Transportation Security Administration (TSA), https://www.tsa.gov/coronavirus/passenger-throughput. Should this URL change or move locations a new URL on the tsa.gov domain will remain valid to resolve this market. 

This market will resolve to “Yes” if the TSA reports a daily checkpoint throughput of more than 2,500,000 for any day between July 8, 2022 and July 31, 2022 (inclusive). Otherwise, this market will resolve to “No”. This market may not resolve to "No" until data for July 31, 2022 is available.

This market will resolve as soon as throughput data becomes available for the date of July 31, 2022, or on any date before that if the target number is reached. If the target number has not been reached and if data is not available for any of the days from July 8, 2022 to July 31, 2022, by August 7, 2022, the market will resolve to 50-50.  Any revisions published to data for dates July 8, 2022 and onward prior to the release of data for July 31, 2022 will be considered.

title: Will Celsius announce bankruptcy by July 13?
description:
In Response to Trader Inquiry: If any subsidiary or parent of Celsius Network LLC announces bankruptcy by the resolution date, it will suffice to resolve this market to "Yes".

On Sunday, June 12, 2022, the Celsius Network (celsius.network) announced that it is suspending all withdrawals, Swaps, and transfers between accounts indefinitely "due to extreme market conditions". Celsius is one of the largest cryptocurrency platforms in the market, and is estimated to have 1.7 million customers.

You can find "A Memo to the Celsius Community" which details the extent of their actions and their reasoning here: https://blog.celsius.network/a-memo-to-the-celsius-community-59532a06ecc6

This market will resolve to "Yes" if Celsius Lending LLC announces that it will declare bankruptcy, is declaring bankruptcy, or has declared bankruptcy of any variety by July 13, 2022, 11:59:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

For a positive resolution to this market to occur, Celsius need only announce that they will declare bankruptcy, are declaring bankruptcy, or have declared bankruptcy by the resolution date, regardless of whether bankruptcy is actually declared at any time.

An "announcement by Celsius" must be made through any of their official or verified channels (https://celsius.network/, https://twitter.com/celsiusnetwork, https://blog.celsius.network/, https://www.instagram.com/celsiusnetwork/, etc.), as a recorded or written statement by their CEO, legal representation, or other individual or team which officially represents Celsius Lending LLC. A consensus of credible reporting may also be used to determine whether Celsius has issued such an announcement.
